title: Add Duning's Log-likelihood hypothesis test for Collocation pruning method
body: Users primarily from a probabilistic background may be more comfortable pruning and identifying collocating bi-grams with a formal hypothesis test such as Duning's LLR, rather than using the heuristic measures currently provided. More on this hypothesis test may be read [here](https://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=972454). [Some research](http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.11.8101&rep=rep1&type=pdf) has shown the LLR scores to be ordinally similar to LMFD.

body:
@dselivanov This is a revision of the README along the lines of what I did for the vignettes.

Some suggestions:
- Should the links to the tutorials be replace with links to or instructions on how to get to the vignettes? Seems like the vignettes are less likely to be out of date.
- You have a discussion of the Corpus object under "Terminology." I think you could cut the whole terminology section since it is out of date for 0.3 and since it's too much information for a README.

Going to work on function level documentation next.

title: Revise 0.3 docs
body:
I'm sending this PR now because I've gone through the vignettes. (Still have to go through the documentation.

Besides revising the language for clarity, the biggest change I made to the introductory vignette was taking advantage of the feature that creates rownames in the DTM.

There is code in the GloVe vignette which does not run because of changed function names. You might want to check that vignette by running all the code, since it won't be checked automatically.

I think the introductory vignette would be improved by having an example of creating a corpus from files on disk.

There is a lot of mismatch between the announcement post for text2vec 0.3 and this branch. I think that has to do with changed function names.

title: Fix width of progress bars
body:
The width of progress bars is currently hardcoded as 100 characters. By
removing this option, the default `width = NA` option means that the
width that users have set with `options()` will be respected. In my
case, that means no overflow of the progress bar.
